(42, 22, 38, 40, 26, 52, 54, 'two swords', 'Connection of Swords and Violence', 'This connection highlights the theme of swords and their implications. In Luke, the mention of ''two swords'' suggests readiness for conflict, while Matthew emphasizes the futility of violence, stating ''all they that take the sword shall perish with the sword.''', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
