(42, 22, 39, 40, 26, 30, 30, 'mount of Olives', 'Journey to the Mount of Olives', 'Both passages emphasize the act of going to the mount of Olives, highlighting a significant location in the narrative. The disciples'' following in Luke parallels the action of going out in Matthew, linking the two events.', 'parallel', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 22, 39, 41, 14, 32, 34, 'to the mount of Olives', 'Connection of Prayer in Gethsemane', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' actions in a garden setting where he goes to pray. Luke mentions the mount of Olives, while Mark specifies Gethsemane, indicating a shared location for this significant moment.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
