(42, 22, 40, 40, 26, 36, 46, 'pray that ye enter not into temptation', 'Connection of Prayer and Temptation', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of prayer in resisting temptation. Jesus instructs his disciples to ''pray that ye enter not into temptation'' in Luke, and similarly urges them to ''watch and pray, that ye enter not into temptation'' in Matthew.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 22, 40, 41, 14, 32, 42, 'Pray that ye enter not into temptation', 'Connection of Prayer and Temptation', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of prayer to avoid temptation. In Luke, Jesus instructs his disciples to pray to not enter into temptation, while in Mark, he reiterates this by urging them to watch and pray for the same reason.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 22, 40, 42, 22, 46, 46, 'pray that ye enter not into temptation', 'Connection of Prayer and Temptation', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of prayer to avoid temptation. The repeated call to ''pray'' highlights the necessity of vigilance in spiritual matters.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 22, 40, 47, 12, 7, 10, 'Pray that ye enter not into temptation', 'Connection of Temptation and Weakness', 'This connection highlights the theme of reliance on divine strength in the face of temptation and weakness. Both passages emphasize the need for prayer and grace to overcome challenges, illustrating how human frailty can lead to spiritual strength.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 22, 40, 49, 6, 18, 19, 'Pray that ye enter not into temptation', 'Connection of Prayer and Temptation', 'This connection highlights the importance of prayer in resisting temptation and spiritual vigilance. Both passages emphasize the need for prayer, with Luke urging to ''pray that ye enter not into temptation'' and Ephesians encouraging ''praying always'' for strength.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 22, 40, 60, 4, 7, 7, 'Pray that ye enter not into temptation', 'Connection of Prayer and Vigilance', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of prayer in facing challenges. Luke 22:40 encourages prayer to avoid temptation, while 1 Peter 4:7 calls for vigilance and prayer as the end approaches.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 22, 41, 40, 26, 39, 39, 'kneeled down, and prayed', 'Prayer in Gethsemane', 'Both passages emphasize the act of prayer during a moment of deep distress. Luke describes Jesus kneeling down to pray, while Matthew highlights his posture of falling on his face in prayer.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 22, 41, 41, 14, 35, 35, 'kneeled down, and prayed', 'Prayer in Gethsemane', 'Both passages emphasize the act of prayer during a moment of distress. They depict Jesus withdrawing from his disciples to seek solitude in prayer, highlighting his emotional struggle.', 'parallel', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 22, 41, 42, 18, 11, 11, 'kneeled down, and prayed', 'Prayer and Humility Connection', 'This connection highlights the act of prayer in both passages. In Luke 22:41, Jesus kneels to pray, while in Luke 18:11, the Pharisee stands to pray, contrasting their attitudes towards God.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 22, 42, 43, 12, 27, 28, NULL, 'Connection of Suffering and Purpose', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of being troubled and the struggle with impending suffering. In Luke, Jesus expresses a desire for the cup to be removed, while in John, he acknowledges his troubled soul but affirms his purpose for coming to this hour.', 'theme', 0.51, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
