(42, 22, 42, 41, 14, 36, 36, 'remove this cup from me', 'Connection in Prayer and Submission', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of submission to God''s will in the face of impending suffering. The phrases ''remove this cup from me'' and ''not my will, but thine'' highlight a deep struggle with the forthcoming events while ultimately yielding to divine authority.', 'theme', 0.43999999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 22, 42, 19, 40, 8, 8, 'not my will, but thine, be done', 'Will of God Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of submitting to God''s will. Both passages express a desire to align personal intentions with divine purpose, emphasizing obedience to God''s law and will.', 'theme', 0.43299999999999994, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
