(42, 22, 42, 43, 18, 11, 11, NULL, 'Connection of the Cup Motif', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of the ''cup'' that Jesus is to drink, highlighting his submission to the Father''s will. In Luke, Jesus expresses a desire for the cup to be removed, while in John, he affirms his commitment to drink it as given by the Father.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
